---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Documentation" description="Complete documentation and API reference for the Camera Mod">
  <section class="docs-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Documentation</h1>
      <p class="intro-text">Comprehensive guide to using and developing with the Camera Mod.</p>

      <div class="docs-grid">
        <!-- Quick Start -->
        <div class="doc-card">
          <h2>🚀 Quick Start</h2>
          <p>Get up and running with the Camera Mod in 5 minutes.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Basic camera controls</li>
            <li>Using presets</li>
            <li>First recording</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="#quick-start" class="doc-link">Read Guide →</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Camera Controls -->
        <div class="doc-card">
          <h2>⌨️ Camera Controls</h2>
          <p>Learn all the keybindings and control options available.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Movement controls</li>
            <li>Preset selection</li>
            <li>Parameter adjustment</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="#controls" class="doc-link">Read Guide →</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Presets Guide -->
        <div class="doc-card">
          <h2>📐 Camera Presets</h2>
          <p>Explore all available camera presets and when to use them.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Static preset</li>
            <li>Cinematic preset</li>
            <li>Orbit preset</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="#presets" class="doc-link">Read Guide →</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Configuration -->
        <div class="doc-card">
          <h2>⚙️ Configuration</h2>
          <p>Customize the mod to your preferences.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Config file location</li>
            <li>Settings reference</li>
            <li>Custom keybinds</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="#config" class="doc-link">Read Guide →</a>
        </div>

        <!-- API Reference -->
        <div class="doc-card">
          <h2>🔌 API Reference</h2>
          <p>For developers: integrate Camera Mod with your mods.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Camera events</li>
            <li>Code examples</li>
            <li>Integration guide</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="#api" class="doc-link">Read Guide →</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Troubleshooting -->
        <div class="doc-card">
          <h2>🐛 Troubleshooting</h2>
          <p>Common issues and how to fix them.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Performance issues</li>
            <li>Compatibility problems</li>
            <li>Configuration help</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="#troubleshooting" class="doc-link">Read Guide →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Detailed Sections -->
      <div class="docs-content">
        
        <!-- Quick Start -->
        <section id="quick-start" class="doc-section">
          <h2>🚀 Quick Start Guide</h2>
          
          <h3>Basic Setup</h3>
          <p>After installing the mod, you're ready to use it immediately:</p>
          <ol>
            <li>Open a Minecraft world</li>
            <li>Press <code>C</code> to open the Camera Menu</li>
            <li>Select a preset (e.g., "Cinematic")</li>
            <li>Use arrow keys to move the camera</li>
            <li>Press <code>Space</code> to start recording (if using recording software)</li>
          </ol>

          <h3>Your First Shot</h3>
          <pre><code>// Basic camera movement
Left/Right Arrows  - Rotate horizontally
Up/Down Arrows     - Rotate vertically
WASD               - Move position
Shift + Move       - Fast movement
Space              - Lock/unlock camera</code></pre>
        </section>

        <!-- Controls -->
        <section id="controls" class="doc-section">
          <h2>⌨️ Camera Controls Reference</h2>
          
          <h3>Primary Controls</h3>
          <table class="controls-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Key</th>
                <th>Action</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><code>C</code></td>
                <td>Open/Close Camera Menu</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>↑ ↓ ← →</code></td>
                <td>Rotate camera view</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>W A S D</code></td>
                <td>Move camera position</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>Shift + Move</code></td>
                <td>Faster movement (3x speed)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>Space</code></td>
                <td>Toggle camera lock</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>1-5</code></td>
                <td>Quick select preset</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </section>

        <!-- Presets -->
        <section id="presets" class="doc-section">
          <h2>📐 Camera Presets</h2>
          
          <h3>Available Presets</h3>
          
          <div class="preset-item">
            <h4>Static</h4>
            <p>A fixed camera position. Perfect for establishing shots and showcasing your builds from a specific angle.</p>
            <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Building showcases, cinematic cutscenes, wide landscape shots</p>
          </div>

          <div class="preset-item">
            <h4>Cinematic</h4>
            <p>Smooth tracking movements with professional easing. Great for following action or panning across scenes.</p>
            <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Gameplay footage, trailers, smooth transitions, action sequences</p>
          </div>

          <div class="preset-item">
            <h4>Orbit</h4>
            <p>The camera orbits around a point of interest. Ideal for 360° showcases and dynamic angles.</p>
            <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Building showcases, item displays, 360° rotations, dramatic reveals</p>
          </div>

          <div class="preset-item">
            <h4>Side Profile</h4>
            <p>Fixed side view for showcasing the profile of your builds.</p>
            <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Architecture showcases, side-view builds, structure demonstrations</p>
          </div>

          <div class="preset-item">
            <h4>Top-Down</h4>
            <p>Overhead perspective for bird's eye view. Perfect for showing layouts and planning.</p>
            <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Base layouts, town planning, aerial photography, map overviews</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Configuration -->
        <section id="config" class="doc-section">
          <h2>⚙️ Configuration</h2>
          
          <h3>Config File Location</h3>
          <div class="code-block">
<pre>Windows: %appdata%/.minecraft/config/cameramod.json
Mac: ~/Library/Application Support/minecraft/config/cameramod.json
Linux: ~/.minecraft/config/cameramod.json</pre>
          </div>

          <h3>Configuration Options</h3>
          <pre><code>{
  "camera": {
    "moveSpeed": 1.0,      // Camera movement speed multiplier
    "rotateSpeed": 1.0,    // Rotation speed multiplier
    "smoothing": 0.8,      // Movement smoothing (0-1)
    "fov": 90              // Field of view
  },
  "controls": {
    "menuKey": "C",
    "fastMoveModifier": "SHIFT"
  },
  "features": {
    "enableOptimization": true,
    "enablePrivacyMode": true
  }
}</code></pre>
        </section>

        <!-- API -->
        <section id="api" class="doc-section">
          <h2>🔌 Developer API</h2>
          
          <h3>Listening to Camera Events (Java)</h3>
          <pre><code>import net.creatortools.camera.CameraEvent;
import net.fabricmc.fabric.api.event.Event;

Event.listen(CameraEvent.MOVE, (camera) → {
  // Called when camera moves
});

Event.listen(CameraEvent.PRESET_CHANGED, (preset) → {
  // Called when preset changes
});</code></pre>

          <h3>Getting Camera State (Java)</h3>
          <pre><code>import net.creatortools.camera.CameraManager;

CameraManager manager = CameraManager.getInstance();
Vec3d position = manager.getPosition();
Quaternion rotation = manager.getRotation();
String currentPreset = manager.getCurrentPreset();</code></pre>
        </section>

        <!-- Troubleshooting -->
        <section id="troubleshooting" class="doc-section">
          <h2>🐛 Troubleshooting</h2>
          
          <h3>Common Issues</h3>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h4>Camera menu won't open</h4>
            <p>Make sure your hotkey isn't bound to another mod or game action. Check your configuration file and try rebinding. Alternatively, use the alternative hotkey.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h4>Mod causes lag</h4>
            <p>Try disabling the optimization features or reducing camera update frequency. The mod is lightweight but may conflict with other rendering mods.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h4>Presets behave differently than expected</h4>
            <p>Check your camera settings. Some presets have different behavior based on configuration values like moveSpeed and smoothing.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h4>Camera is shaking or jittering</h4>
            <p>Increase the smoothing value in your configuration. Also check that you don't have conflicting camera mods installed.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Need More Help -->
      <div class="help-section">
        <h3>Still need help?</h3>
        <p>Check out our community resources or report an issue on GitHub.</p>
        <div class="help-links">
          <a href="#">GitHub Repository</a>
          <a href="#">Discord Community</a>
          <a href="#">Issue Tracker</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .docs-section {
      padding: var(--spacing-3xl) var(--spacing-md);
    }

    .docs-section h1 {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    }

    .intro-text {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 1.125rem;
      color: #64748b;
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3xl);
    }

    .docs-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
      gap: var(--spacing-xl);
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3xl);
    }

    .doc-card {
      padding: var(--spacing-xl);
      background: white;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 0.75rem;
      transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }

    .doc-card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-4px);
      box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      border-color: var(--color-primary);
    }

    .doc-card h2 {
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
      color: var(--color-primary);
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }

    .doc-card p {
      color: #64748b;
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .doc-card ul {
      list-style: none;
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    }

    .doc-card ul li {
      padding-left: var(--spacing-lg);
      position: relative;
      color: #64748b;
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .doc-card ul li:before {
      content: "•";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: var(--color-secondary);
    }

    .doc-link {
      display: inline-block;
      color: var(--color-primary);
      font-weight: 600;
      transition: all 0.2s ease;
    }

    .doc-link:hover {
      color: var(--color-secondary);
    }

    .docs-content {
      margin: var(--spacing-3xl) 0;
    }

    .doc-section {
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3xl);
      padding: var(--spacing-2xl);
      background: white;
      border-radius: 0.75rem;
      border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    }

    .doc-section h2 {
      color: var(--color-primary);
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
    }

    .doc-section h3 {
      color: var(--color-primary);
      margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    }

    .doc-section h4 {
      color: var(--color-dark);
      margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    }

    .doc-section p {
      color: #475569;
    }

    .doc-section ol, .doc-section ul {
      margin-left: var(--spacing-lg);
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    }

    .doc-section li {
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
      color: #475569;
    }

    .code-block {
      background: #f1f5f9;
      padding: var(--spacing-lg);
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
      margin: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
      overflow-x: auto;
    }

    .controls-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
    }

    .controls-table thead {
      background: #f1f5f9;
    }

    .controls-table th,
    .controls-table td {
      padding: var(--spacing-md);
      text-align: left;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    .controls-table code {
      background: white;
      border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    }

    .preset-item {
      margin: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
      padding: var(--spacing-lg);
      background: #f8fafc;
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
    }

    .preset-item h4 {
      color: var(--color-primary);
    }

    .faq-item {
      margin: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
    }

    .faq-item h4 {
      color: var(--color-secondary);
    }

    .help-section {
      text-align: center;
      padding: var(--spacing-2xl);
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-accent) 0%, var(--color-primary) 100%);
      color: white;
      border-radius: 0.75rem;
      margin-top: var(--spacing-3xl);
    }

    .help-section h3 {
      color: white;
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    }

    .help-links {
      display: flex;
      gap: var(--spacing-lg);
      justify-content: center;
      margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .help-links a {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: var(--spacing-md) var(--spacing-xl);
      background: white;
      color: var(--color-primary);
      border-radius: 0.375rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      transition: all 0.2s ease;
    }

    .help-links a:hover {
      background: #f1f5f9;
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .docs-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .controls-table {
        font-size: 0.875rem;
      }

      .help-links {
        flex-direction: column;
      }

      .help-links a {
        width: 100%;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
